This paper deals with motion planning for legged robots, which is a core problem in robotics. The paper specifically focuses on humanoid robots, which are a subset of legged robots. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also introduces a new concept called the "Possibility Graph", which is a high-level approximation of constraint manifolds. This concept is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG), as it involves exploring the possibility of actions. The paper also uses computer vision (cs.CV) to analyze the environments and identify obstacles. Finally, the paper deals with motion planning, which is a control problem, and therefore, it is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
